The paper proposes a method for image synthesis using hierarchical AND-OR networks, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The method involves end-to-end training with sparsity-inducing constraints, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convolutional neural networks is also a common technique in both computer vision and machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of hyperparameters, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the representation and manipulation of graphs, which is a topic related to computer graphics (cs.GR).
